{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel0 \b \fs36 Codex System Contract (LOCKED)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 This document defines the {\b global, non-negotiable invariants} of the Paperhat Codex system.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 It applies to:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab all Paperhat libraries\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab all generated applications\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab all tooling\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab all LLM implementers\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 This document is {\b normative}.\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 1. Core Philosophy (Hard)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 1.1 Everything Is Data\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab All authored meaning is expressed as data.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Behavior, validation, state transitions, and rendering are described declaratively.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Code exists only to execute, never to encode meaning.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 1.2 Single Sources of Truth\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Applications:} CDX files under version control are the single source of truth.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Libraries:} Ontologies, constraints, and semantics live in libraries and are compiled into runtime stores.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Runtime stores:} Triple stores are compiled artifacts, never authoritative sources.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 1.3 Referential Transparency\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab All semantic functions are pure.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Given the same inputs, the same outputs are produced.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab No hidden state, no ambient context, no mutation.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 1.4 IO Is Isolated\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab IO is explicitly separated from pure computation.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab IO boundaries are narrow, explicit, and owned by specific libraries.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Pure code must never perform IO.\sa180\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 2. Authoring Surface (Hard)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 2.1 CDX Is the Only Authoring Language\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Application developers write {\b only CDX}.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab No imports, no exports, no user-authored functions.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab No JavaScript or TypeScript in applications (except static assets).\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 2.2 Declarative Only\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab No imperative control flow in authored content.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab All logic is expressed via composition.\sa180\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 3. The Canonical Pipeline (Hard)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 All meaning flows through the same pipeline:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 CDX \u8594 ? AST \u8594 ? IR \u8594 ? RDF / Turtle \u8594 ? Triple Store (Oxigraph) \u8594 ? SPARQL \u8594 ? ViewModel \u8594 ? Render Target\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Parsing, compilation, storage, querying, and rendering are distinct phases.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Short-circuit paths (e.g.\u160 ?Dev modes) must preserve semantic equivalence.\sa180\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 4. Purity and the Three-Path Rule (Hard)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 4.1 The Three Paths\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Any operation that can fail must return one of:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Usable(value)} \u8212- successful result\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Helps([\u8230 ?])} \u8212- one or more help messages\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Pending} \u8212- computation not yet complete\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Exceptions are forbidden.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 4.2 Universal Return Shape\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 At runtime, all evaluatable operations return:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \f1 Future<Validation<Help, A>>;\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Async is universal.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Laziness is preferred.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Pending is not failure.\sa180\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 5. Toolsmith as Kernel (Hard)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 5.1 Shared Foundations\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 All shared primitives live in {\b Toolsmith}, including:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab monads\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab combinators\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab newtype machinery\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab BaseHelp\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab help construction utilities\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab numeric and structural types\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 No other library may reimplement these.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 5.2 Extension, Not Duplication\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Libraries may:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab extend BaseHelp with local codes\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab define library-specific newtypes using Toolsmith primitives\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Libraries may not:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab inspect monad internals\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab bypass Toolsmith abstractions\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab introduce ad-hoc error handling\sa180\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 6. Folder Structure and Privacy (Hard)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 6.1 Public vs Private\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Any folder prefixed with {\f1 _} is private.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Private folders are internal implementation details.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Public API surface must be explicit and minimal.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 6.2 Lowest Common Ancestor Rule\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Shared internal implementation lives at the lowest common ancestor.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab No junk-drawer folders.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab No \u8220"utils\u8221", \u8220"misc\u8221", or catch-alls.\sa180\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 7. Runtime Model (Hard)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 7.1 Async and Lazy by Default\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab All runtime evaluation is async.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Evaluation is lazy and demand-driven.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 7.2 Event-Driven Execution\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Runtime execution is driven by events, not direct calls.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Event delegation is used; per-element handlers are avoided.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 (See Engine Contract for details.)\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 8. Help System and Pedagogy (Hard)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 8.1 Errors Become Help\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab All failures are represented as Help.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab No error is silent.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab No error is thrown.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 8.2 Pedagogical Tone\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Help messages must:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab use \u8220"we\u8221"\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab be polite and non-blaming\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab explain what happened\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab explain why\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab suggest next steps\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The system teaches; it does not scold.\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 9. Agile but Disciplined\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Contracts are living documents.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Changes are allowed, but must be explicit.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Major semantic changes trigger rewrites and archival of prior versions.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Implementation follows contracts, never precedes them.\sa180\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 Status\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 LOCKED.\par}
}
